00184 typedef struct ArrayModifierData {
00185     ModifierData modifier;
00186 
00187     /* the object with which to cap the start of the array  */
00188     struct Object *start_cap;
00189     /* the object with which to cap the end of the array  */
00190     struct Object *end_cap;
00191     /* the curve object to use for MOD_ARR_FITCURVE */
00192     struct Object *curve_ob;
00193     /* the object to use for object offset */
00194     struct Object *offset_ob;
00195     /* a constant duplicate offset;
00196      * 1 means the duplicates are 1 unit apart
00197      */
00198     float offset[3];
00199     /* a scaled factor for duplicate offsets;
00200      * 1 means the duplicates are 1 object-width apart
00201      */
00202     float scale[3];
00203     /* the length over which to distribute the duplicates */
00204     float length;
00205     /* the limit below which to merge vertices in adjacent duplicates */
00206     float merge_dist;
00207     /* determines how duplicate count is calculated; one of:
00208      * - MOD_ARR_FIXEDCOUNT -> fixed
00209      * - MOD_ARR_FITLENGTH  -> calculated to fit a set length
00210      * - MOD_ARR_FITCURVE   -> calculated to fit the length of a Curve object
00211      */
00212     int fit_type;
00213     /* flags specifying how total offset is calculated; binary OR of:
00214      * - MOD_ARR_OFF_CONST    -> total offset += offset
00215      * - MOD_ARR_OFF_RELATIVE -> total offset += relative * object width
00216      * - MOD_ARR_OFF_OBJ      -> total offset += offset_ob's matrix
00217      * total offset is the sum of the individual enabled offsets
00218      */
00219     int offset_type;
00220     /* general flags:
00221      * MOD_ARR_MERGE -> merge vertices in adjacent duplicates
00222      */
00223     int flags;
00224     /* the number of duplicates to generate for MOD_ARR_FIXEDCOUNT */
00225     int count;
00226 } ArrayModifierData;
00227 
00228 /* ArrayModifierData->fit_type */
00229 #define MOD_ARR_FIXEDCOUNT 0
00230 #define MOD_ARR_FITLENGTH  1
00231 #define MOD_ARR_FITCURVE   2
00232 
00233 /* ArrayModifierData->offset_type */
00234 #define MOD_ARR_OFF_CONST    (1<<0)
00235 #define MOD_ARR_OFF_RELATIVE (1<<1)
00236 #define MOD_ARR_OFF_OBJ      (1<<2)
00237 
00238 /* ArrayModifierData->flags */
00239 #define MOD_ARR_MERGE      (1<<0)
00240 #define MOD_ARR_MERGEFINAL (1<<1)
